-- Nigeria’s Naira Moves Between Gains and Losses Against Dollar
-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 2012-03-01T13:16:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-01/nigeria-s-naira-moves-between-gains-and-losses-against-dollar.html
The naira moved between gains and
losses against the dollar on the  interbank market .  The currency of  Africa ’s biggest oil producer weakened less
than 0.1 percent to 157.665 per dollar as of 1:20 p.m.,
according to data compiled by Bloomberg. The naira strengthened
as much as 0.8 percent to 156.4 in Lagos, the commercial capital  The surge in inflation in January to 12.6 percent from 10.3
percent in December was in line with policy makers’ expectations
and doesn’t require an interest rate response, Nigerian central
bank Governor Lamido Sanusi said Feb. 28.  Ghana’s cedi strengthened 0.1 percent to 1.7009 per dollar
as of 12:20 p.m. in Accra, the capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
